      "id": "690530c7-c3ae-5e3b-a756-0336fb5e19c3",
      "label": "TextSummary_690530c7-c3ae-5e3b-a756-0336fb5e19c3",
      "type": "TextSummary",
      "properties": {
        "text": "Swarnendu Bhandari's resume details his education, projects, awards, skills, and contact information.\n- From Nov 2022 to present, he is pursuing a combined B.Tech and M.Tech degree at IIT Kharagpur with a CGPA of 8.26/10.\n- In 2022, he completed his Class XII board exam at Krishnath College School, scoring 93.8%.\n- In 2020, he completed his Class X board exam at Panchthupi T.N. Institution, scoring 84.7%.\n- From Dec 2025 to present, he led the InfuseAI project as Platform Architect and Team Leader, designing a Retrieval‑Augmented Generation pipeline, cloud‑native architecture, developer SDK, and documentation using RAG, LLMs, and Pinecone.\n- From Feb 2025 to Sep 2025, he developed Dmaid.cloud, an AI‑powered Mermaid diagram editor that integrates Llama 4 and DeepSeek R1 LLMs, supports export to SVG, HTML, and Markdown, provides undo/redo for up to 300 states, and uses Firebase Google Sign‑In for user authentication.\n- He engineered the Orbit AI Workspace travel platform, building a Next.js 16, TypeScript front‑end with Framer Motion and Tailwind CSS, a MongoDB/Mongoose back‑end, Firebase AuthGuard security, Zustand state management, and integration of the Tambo AI SDK and Tiptap for collaborative editing.\n- In Jan 2026, he received the Best Deep Tech Idea award in the Entrepreneurship Launchpad Programme at RMSoEE, IIT Kharagpur for the InfuseAI concept.\n- In Jan 2026, he won the Vercel Track at AI Agents Assemble 2025 hosted by WeMakeDevs Community, earning $2,000 funding for InfuseAI.\n- He possesses expertise in frameworks and libraries such as Next.js, React.js, Prisma, Numpy, Pandas, Express.js, OpenAPI Spec, Mongoose, and Socket.io; programming languages including Typescript, Python, C, Rust, Java, Javascript, and Solidity; and tools/platforms like Git, Docker, Bash, Postman, Linux, Firebase, Google Gemini APIs, Cloudflare, MongoDB Atlas, and various LLM APIs.\n- He can be contacted at +91 8101199607, email clickswarnendu123@gmail.com, GitHub username swarnendu_, and is based in Kharagpur, West Bengal, India.",
